The paper deals with the recognition of fan-planar and maximal outer fan-planar graphs, which are topics related to computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT). The algorithm presented in the paper involves polynomial-time testing, which suggests that it may also be relevant to algorithms and complexity (cs.DS) and theoretical computer science (cs.TC). Finally, the paper discusses the NP-hardness of testing fan-planarity, which could also place it in the sub-category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
